09/04/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The joint EU-Romania Parliamentary Committee has issued 24 recommendations to help Romania adhere to the timetable for EU accession, according to media reports Friday (9 April). The panel's recommendations include measures for combating corruption, improving the judicial system, eliminating conflicts of interest and amending the law on political parties.
In other news, the Romanian government endorsed a co-operation agreement Thursday with EUROPOL and forwarded the draft to parliament for ratification. (Gardianul, Rompres - 09/04/04)
